{
  "stem": "10181.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then later on, there was-- by the way, these 222 Jews were exchanged for German Templers who were living in Palestine from-- from long before the war and had been interned by the British.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And for some reason, 1944, the German government wanted them back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "You know, that's unimportant anyway.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So that's how they managed to-- to leave Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Then there was supposed to be an exchange through Switzerland, and some people were called for that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We weren't, but some people were called for that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "A-- I don't know how many, a few, and they were put on the train.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They didn't make it to Switzerland because there was some hitch developed in-- in the exchange.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But they weren't sent back to Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They were sent to a different camp near the Swiss border, like a-- internment-- internment camp.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It wasn't as bad as Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Then the-- the commandant changed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got Josef Kramer to be the commandant of Bergen-Belsen, and he had been in Auschwitz, OK?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he decided that Bergen-Belsen was a concentration camp, and if-- you know, this is what it's supposed to be, and this is what it's going to be.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the meanwhile, towards the fall of 1944, many more people arrived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, we got more people coming from Holland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We got some people from France who came into our camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From-- Greek, a few more Greeks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nothing which was happening-- I explained to you at the beginning that the Greeks were in charge who from Salonica who had been there before us who received all the food and were corrupt.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and-- and where the-- the-- the Jewish commandant was a Greek, and there were--.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In the summer, in the middle of the summer, the Germans decided that they were too corrupt or whatever.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know how-- I mean, how they came to that conclusion.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, they were obviously, but they got rid of them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, they weren't going to allow them to run the camp anymore.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they brought in kapos, you know, kapos from outside, not from within-- non-Jewish, mostly Poles, non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And like I said, and-- to run the camp from within.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember the picture of-- there was constant roll call that day when it happened.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was like a revolution, internal revolution.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Nobody knew quite what was happening.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I remember the-- the Greeks hiding in our barracks because they were afraid.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they didn't go out to roll call because they were afraid of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So we hid them in the barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I mean, I didn't, but they were hidden by-- by some of our people in the barracks.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And of course, they kept a low profile because they were afraid that the Germans would take them away from Bergen-Belsen and send them somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then-- this was at the time already of Kramer, OK?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, aside from the new people coming into our camp, people were coming from east-- from the east on those famous death-- or infamous death marches-- or by trains from the camps which were being-- you know, they were close to the front, including Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And by October, November of 1944, not only were conditions bad, they were worse, became worse, because they took away some of our barracks and made us double and triple up, you know, [? instead ?] of-- the bunks at the beginning were three-- three high, you know, with straw mattresses.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They became four or five high.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know how they held up and didn't fall over, but they did.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I guess they were next to each other so they wouldn't fall over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And sometimes for smaller, were two or three to a-- to a bunk.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The food got to be worse, if that's possible, but it did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We got maybe one piece of bread a week.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We did get this rotten soup-- it was frozen turnip soup== every day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Also, these-- like I said, the sanitary conditions were very bad.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They got worse because less barracks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were no-- there no-- no washrooms.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "People started getting sick.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And people were dying from the typhus, you know, because we-- we-- we had lice.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had lice all over, you know, slowly but surely.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I think the lice came originally, probably, with the beds, and I'm sure they were in there already.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the-- we-- we had no way of getting rid of them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And you know, lice spread disease.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And one of the diseases which were-- which [INAUDIBLE] made Bergen-Belsen so bad was typhus.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You know, it's-- it's a-- it's a deadly disease.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Many people died or were dying.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
